name: Government shutdown
summary: The United States government faces an impending shutdown as Congress grapples with passing a funding bill. The Republican-led House of Representatives voted against a temporary spending measure proposed by Speaker Nancy Pelosi, while Senate Republicans are losing patience with Senator Ron Johnson, who is advocating for stricter measures. Despite efforts by House Democrats to avert the shutdown, negotiations seem to be failing, with House Minority Leader Hakeem Jeffries setting clear boundaries against any concessions. As the deadline approaches, the House is expected to vote again on a doomed spending bill proposed by the GOP, which is unlikely to pass. Johnson has dodged questions about the consequences of a shutdown if the spending bill fails, while the government shutdown standoff continues to linger in Congress.

name: 23andMe
summary: 23andMe has faced significant challenges recently. The company has agreed to pay a $30 million settlement over a data breach that affected 6.9 million users. This has led to the resignation of the entire board of directors, who were rebuking CEO Anne Wojcicki's takeover plan. Wojcicki has expressed "surprise and disappointment" over these resignations, but still intends to take the company private. The company has also settled a data breach lawsuit for $30 million and has pledged $30 million to those affected by the breach. Despite these challenges, Wojcicki remains committed to the company and its mission.
